Judgment is expected to be handed down in 52-year-old Tinyiko Khosa&#8217;s bail application. JOHANNESBURG Judgment is expected to be handed down in the Giyani Magistrates Court today in the bail application of 52-year-old Tinyiko Khosa, who is believed to be behind the Limpopo exam leak scandal.Khosa was arrested last week after the Hawks launched an investigation.He s believed to have masterminded the distribution of the Mathematics paper, which was shared amongst pupils before the exam took place last month.Khosa will find out today whether he will be granted bail after his case was postponed on Wednesday. The Limpopo businessman, who owns two colleges in Malamulele, allegedly leaked the Mathematics paper in Limpopo, which was shared amongst some pupils via WhatsApp.Khosa faces several counts including fraud and corruption.The Basic Education Department says it believes the suspect is part of a syndicate which they believe has been undermining the National Senior Certificate exams.The department says it hopes his arrest will lead to officials to other perpetrators.(Edited by Leeto M Khoza)